','',168,'http://include.xyz/2019/05/17/168-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(174,1,'2019-05-17 10:28:16','2019-05-17 10:28:16','<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>INCLUDE: A learning resource for managers of CBR and other development programmes</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<div class=\"row\"><div class=\"col-md-8\">INCLUDE contains 8 modules of information that will help you learn about CBR and how to implement inclusive development principles in your programme.&nbsp;<em>To view any of the modules (shown below), select its picture.</em></div>\n<div class=\"col-md-4\"><button class=\"learn-more ml-learn\">How to use this course</button></div></div>\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;The modules can be viewed in any order; however we recommend that you start with the Introduction module.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Module Library','','inherit','closed','closed','','168-revision-v1','','','2019-05-17 10:28:16','2019-05-17 10:28:16','',168,'http://include.xyz/2019/05/17/168-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(175,1,'2019-05-18 18:57:25','2019-05-18 18:57:25','This introductory module introduces community-based rehabilitation (CBR) as a development strategy designed to “make rights real” in keeping with the Convention on the Rights of Persons with Disabilities (CRPD). It also shows users how to navigate through this online learning package.','Introduction','','publish','closed','closed','','introduction','','','2019-05-22 17:24:31','2019-05-22 17:24:31','',0,'http://include.xyz/?post_type=modules&#038;p=175',0,'modules','',0),(176,1,'2019-05-19 21:39:59','2019-05-19 21:39:59','<div class=\"field field-name-field-callout-text field-type-text-long field-label-hidden\">\r\n<div class=\"field-items\">\r\n<div class=\"field-item even\">\r\n<div id=\"page-header\" class=\"row\">\r\n<div id=\"h1-container\" class=\"col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12\">\r\n<h3 class=\"page-header\">Introduction</h3>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\nBefore you begin this module, we urge you to take a few moments to reflect on your expectations about this online course, as well as your previous experience (if any) with CBR.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','Introduction-intro','','publish','closed','closed','','this-is-working-test','','','2019-05-22 17:33:39','2019-05-22 17:33:39','',175,'http://include.xyz/?post_type=modules&#038;p=176',0,'modules','',0),(178,1,'2019-05-20 06:18:51','2019-05-20 06:18:51','This module introduces common strategies that managers of any organization can use to set up a new – or strengthen an existing – programme based on CBR principles.','Management','','publish','closed','closed','','management','','','2019-05-22 17:14:29','2019-05-22 17:14:29','',0,'http://include.xyz/?post_type=modules&#038;p=178',0,'modules','',0),(179,1,'2019-05-20 06:19:54','2019-05-20 06:19:54','CBR programmes support the health and well-being of people with disabilities in five key areas covered in this module: health promotion, prevention, medical care, rehabilitation and assistive devices.','Health','','publish','closed','closed','','health','','','2019-05-20 10:24:41','2019-05-20 10:24:41','',0,'http://include.xyz/?post_type=modules&#038;p=179',0,'modules','',0),(203,1,'2019-05-20 07:08:10','2019-05-20 07:08:10','&nbsp;\r\n<div id=\"h1-container\" class=\"col-lg-10 col-md-10 col-sm-9 col-xs-9\">\r\n<h1 class=\"page-header\">Key messages</h1>\r\n</div>\r\nWelcome to INCLUDE!\r\n\r\nThe key message is to <strong>promote CBR as a strategy</strong> to:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>realize the rights of people with disabilities at the community level;</li>\r\n 	<li>support people with disabilities and their families in getting out of poverty;</li>\r\n 	<li>support stakeholders so that people with disabilities and their families can satisfy their basic needs, improve their daily lives, and access health, education, livelihood, social and other services;</li>\r\n 	<li>promote the empowerment of people with disabilities and their families in their communities; and</li>\r\n 	<li>support decision-making by people with disabilities on an equal basis with others.</li>\r\n</ul>','Introduction-Key messages','','publish','closed','closed','','introduction-key-messages','','','2019-05-20 07:08:10','2019-05-20 07:08:10','',0,'http://include.xyz/?post_type=chapters&#038;p=203',0,'chapters','',0),(204,1,'2019-05-20 07:09:47','2019-05-20 07:09:47','This course consists of the following learning modules:\r\n\r\n<strong>Module 1 – Introduction</strong>\r\n\r\nThe Introduction provides an overview of the concept of disability and its evolution, the Convention on the Rights of Persons with Disabilities (CRPD), the development of CBR leading to the creation of the CBR matrix and the CBR Guidelines.\r\n\r\n<strong>Modules 2–7</strong>\r\n\r\nThese modules begin by examining issues in Management, and then consider in turn each of the five basic components of the CBR Matrix – Health, Education, Livelihood, Social and Empowerment – each of which is broken down into its subcomponents and discussed separately.\r\n\r\n<strong>Module 8</strong>\r\n\r\nThis supplementary module covers four additional topics, not previously considered in CBR: mental health, HIV/AIDS, leprosy and humanitarian crises.','Introduction-Course overview','','publish','closed','closed','','introduction-course-overview','','','2019-05-20 07:09:47','2019-05-20 07:09:47','',0,'http://include.xyz/?post_type=chapters&#038;p=204',0,'chapters','',0),(205,1,'2019-05-20 07:10:36','2019-05-20 07:10:36','<div id=\"node-book-full-group-content-wrapper\" class=\"content-wrapper row\">\r\n<div class=\"field field-name-field-content field-type-text-long field-label-hidden\">\r\n<div class=\"field-items\">\r\n<div class=\"field-item even\">\r\n\r\nThe objectives of this Introduction module are to:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>provide a brief overview of CBR, its history and the CBR Guidelines</li>\r\n 	<li>introduce the evolving concept of disability</li>\r\n 	<li>introduce the Convention on the Rights of Persons with Disabilities</li>\r\n 	<li>look at development and inclusive development</li>\r\n 	<li>look at CBR as a strategy for disability-inclusive development, now and in the future.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','Introduction -Objectives of the Introduction module','','publish','closed','closed','','introduction-objectives-of-the-introduction-module','','','2019-05-20 07:13:03','2019-05-20 07:13:03','',0,'http://include.xyz/?post_type=chapters&#038;p=205',0,'chapters','',0),(206,1,'2019-05-20 07:14:42','2019-05-20 07:14:42','The <a data-toggle=\"modal\" data-target=\".cbr-matrix\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">CBR Matrix</a>, created as part of the CBR Guidelines, has a set of common organizing principles for community-based rehabilitation, which are introduced in this module.\r\n\r\nIt is recognized and expected that each CBR activity is unique and will need to make important decisions based on the human and economic resources available, as well as the economic, political and cultural environment in which the programme must operate. These decisions include:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>which components of the CBR Matrix will need to be implemented to address the needs, priorities and resources of the communities being served?</li>\r\n 	<li>how will the programme need to be adapted to satisfy the cultural values and expectations of the different groups and communities being served?</li>\r\n 	<li>how can the programme be most effectively structured and managed?</li>\r\n</ul>','Management-Introduction to management','','publish','closed','closed','','management-introduction-to-management','','','2019-05-20 07:14:42','2019-05-20 07:14:42','',0,'http://include.xyz/?post_type=chapters&#038;p=206',0,'chapters','',0),(207,1,'2019-05-20 07:15:31','2019-05-20 07:15:31','The material presented in this module is designed to help you adapt your CBR so that it best satisfies the needs, priorities and resources of the communities you serve. Specifically, you will learn how to:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>select the components and elements of the CBR matrix relevant and appropriate to your situation;</li>\r\n 	<li>employ a participatory style of management to increase the inclusiveness and sustainability of your CBR;</li>\r\n 	<li>use a proven four-stage management cycle to engage people with disabilities, their families and governments and funding bodies actively in the CBR process and effectively respond to the needs of people with disabilities and their families; and</li>\r\n 	<li>build a programme aligned with both the CBR Guidelines and the Convention on the Rights of Persons with Disabilities (CRPD).</li>\r\n</ul>','Management -What you will learn in this module','','publish','closed','closed','','management-what-you-will-learn-in-this-module','','','2019-05-20 07:15:31','2019-05-20 07:15:31','',0,'http://include.xyz/?post_type=chapters&#038;p=207',0,'chapters','',0),(208,1,'2019-05-20 07:16:36','2019-05-20 07:16:36','<div id=\"node-book-full-group-calout-inner\" class=\"callout-inner col-xs-12 col-sm-9 col-md-9 col-lg-9\">\r\n<div class=\"field field-name-field-callout-text field-type-text-long field-label-hidden\">\r\n<div class=\"field-items\">\r\n<div class=\"field-item even\">\r\n\r\nA well-managed CBR activity:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>implements the CBR components that best match the needs, priorities and resources of the community;</li>\r\n 	<li>is inclusive of all key community stakeholders, especially people with disabilities, their family members and organizations that represent them; and</li>\r\n 	<li>ensures equal treatment by implementing the rights in the Convention on the Rights of Persons with Disabilities (CRPD).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"node-book-full-group-img-container\" class=\"img-container col-xs-12 col-sm-3 col-md-3 col-lg-3\">\r\n<div class=\"field field-name-field-callout-image field-type-image field-label-hidden\">\r\n<div class=\"field-items\"></div>\r\n</div>