expand the module heading that contains the activity you want. Then select the activity name from the list that appears on the left-hand side of the screen.</em>[contact-form-7 id=\"271\" title=\"Lobby and advocate for inclusion\"]<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','My action plan','','inherit','closed','closed','','42-revision-v1','','','2019-05-29 10:37:52','2019-05-29 10:37:52','',42,'http://include.xyz/2019/05/29/42-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(273,1,'2019-05-29 10:43:49','2019-05-29 10:43:49','<div class=\"intro\"> \r\n<h5><b>Prepare for emergency, conflict and refugee situations</b></h5>\r\n<p>The well-being of the young child is crucial in any emergency, conflict or natural disaster. CBR can help to ensure that there are inclusive child-friendly spaces and opportunities for play activities; this often means interacting with United Nations organizations as well as nongovernmental organizations and government services.</p>\r\n<p><em>Complete the following form to identify the support strategies you believe will work best in your situation. Select Save when you are finished.</em></p>\r\n<p><b>1. Identify resources</b></p>\r\n<p>Identify the United Nations organizations, non-governmental organizations, and government services that could help in a time of crisis:</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\"><b>Organization</b></div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\"><b>Area of focus</b></div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableHead p-2 vertical\"><b>Contact information</b></div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[text text-15 id:cf-265-1 class:cf-265-1]</div> \r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[text text-15 id:cf-265-1 class:cf-265-1]</div> \r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[text text-15 id:cf-265-1 class:cf-265-1]</div> \r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[text text-15 id:cf-265-1 class:cf-265-1]</div> \r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[text text-15 id:cf-265-1 class:cf-265-1]</div> \r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[text text-15 id:cf-265-1 class:cf-265-1]</div> \r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[text text-15 id:cf-265-1 class:cf-265-1]</div> \r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[text text-15 id:cf-265-1 class:cf-265-1]</div> \r\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[text text-15 id:cf-265-1 class:cf-265-1]</div> \r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><b>2. Network and prepare for future emergency</b></p>\r\n<p>Next, take steps to connect and work with these organizations to prepare for situations of emergency. In particular, work with these partners to think about and prepare for ways to sustain early childhood education during these crises. For more information about preparing for and responding to humanitarian crises, see the see the Humanitarian Crises portion of the Supplementary module.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\n1\nINCLUDE: \"[your-subject]\"\nINCLUDE: <wordpress@include.xyz>\nbomoxuxul@parcel4.net\nFrom: [your-name] <[your-email]>\r\nSubject: [your-subject]\r\n\r\nMessage Body:\r\n[your-message]\r\n\r\n-- \r\nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on INCLUDE: (http://include.xyz)\nReply-To: [your-email]\n\n\n\n\nINCLUDE: \"[your-subject]\"\nINCLUDE: <wordpress@include.xyz>\n[your-email]\nMessage Body:\r\n[your-message]\r\n\r\n-- \r\nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on INCLUDE: (http://include.xyz)\nReply-To: bomoxuxul@parcel4.net\n\n\n\nThank you for your message. It has been sent.\nThere was an error trying to send your message. Please try again later.\nOne or more fields have an error. Please check and try again.\nThere was an error trying to send your message. Please try again later.\nYou must accept the terms and conditions before sending your message.\nThe field is required.\nThe field is too long.\nThe field is too short.\nThe date format is incorrect.\nThe date is before the earliest one allowed.\nThe date is after the latest one allowed.\nThere was an unknown error uploading the file.\nYou are not allowed to upload files of this type.\nThe file is too big.\nThere was an error uploading the file.\nThe number format is invalid.\nThe number is smaller than the minimum allowed.\nThe number is larger than the maximum allowed.\nThe answer to the quiz is incorrect.\nYour entered code is incorrect.\nThe e-mail address entered is invalid.\nThe URL is invalid.\nThe telephone number is invalid.','Prepare for emergency, conflict and refugee situations','','publish','closed','closed','','prepare-for-emergency-conflict-and-refugee-situations','','','2019-05-29 10:50:02','2019-05-29 10:50:02','',0,'http://include.xyz/?post_type=wpcf7_contact_form&#038;p=273',0,'wpcf7_contact_form','',0),(274,1,'2019-05-29 10:44:17','2019-05-29 10:44:17','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>To view or modify an activity in your action plan, use your mouse or keyboard to expand the module heading that contains the activity you want. Then select the activity name from the list that appears on the left-hand side of the screen.</em>[contact-form-7 id=\"273\" title=\"Prepare for emergency, conflict and refugee situations\"]<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','My action plan','','inherit','closed','closed','','42-revision-v1','','','2019-05-29 10:44:17','2019-05-29 10:44:17','',42,'http://include.xyz/2019/05/29/42-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(275,1,'2019-05-29 10:50:51','2019-05-29 10:50:51','<div class=\"intro\"> \r\n<h5><b>Address poverty</b></h5>\r\n<p>In poverty situations, when families and communities are struggling to meet their basic needs, children are perceived either as a help towards survival or as a burden because of scarce resources. Children who are hungry and sick due to poverty find it difficult to learn and play. CBR personnel therefore need to address poverty alongside promoting early childhood education.</p>\r\n<p><em>Complete the following form to identify the support strategies you believe will work best in your situation. Select Save when you are finished.</em></p>\r\n<p>There are several things that your organisation can do to help address poverty in the community. Use the following list as a starting point to generate more ideas.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Help families to understand that the earlier children with disabilities are supported in learning self-care and basic skills, the more independent they will become and the less they will be perceived as a burden.</li>\r\n<li>Focus on activities that fit into the daily family routine, and demonstrate how children learn through these activities, so they become an integral part of family life. In situations of extreme poverty, families and particularly mothers need additional support, not additional responsibility, so the attitude of CBR personnel is very important.</li>\r\n<li>Facilitate the development of self-help groups for women and parents of children with disabilities, and disabled people\'s organizations (see Empowerment module).</li>\r\n<li>Help families to access government grants, support from non-governmental organizations, donors and local businesses, and any other sources of support and funding.</li>\r\n<li>Help ensure that early childhood programmes are flexible and respond to the different situations of poor families, including families who have children with severe or multiple impairments.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>What are some other activities that your programme can do?</p>\r\n[textarea textarea-900 id:255-cf class:255-cf cols:130 rows:5]\n1\nINCLUDE: \"[your-subject]\"\nINCLUDE: <wordpress@include.xyz>\nbomoxuxul@parcel4.net\nFrom: [your-name] <[your-email]>\r\nSubject: [your-subject]\r\n\r\nMessage Body:\r\n[your-message]\r\n\r\n-- \r\nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on INCLUDE: (http://include.xyz)\nReply-To: [your-email]\n\n\n\n\nINCLUDE: \"[your-subject]\"\nINCLUDE: <wordpress@include.xyz>\n[your-email]\nMessage Body:\r\n[your-message]\r\n\r\n-- \r\nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on INCL